Title: Matrix Norms and Inequalities with Python
Slug: matrix-norms-inequalities-python
Date: 2020-04-27
Category: Linear Algebra
Tags: Linear Algebra, Python, mathematics
Author: Aaron Schlegel
Summary: Matrix norms are an extension of vector norms to matrices and are used to define a measure of distance on the space of a matrix. The most commonly occurring matrix norms in matrix analysis are the Frobenius, $L_1$, $L_2$ and $L_\infty$ norms. The following will investigate these norms, along with some Python implementations of the calculation of the matrix norm.
